\begin_layout Standard
One of the largest hindrances to ferroelectrics in many applications is
 the susceptibility of ferroelectric films to aging and fatigue.
 Aging is the slow changing of a material's characteristics over time, while
 fatigue takes place under high electric field.
 Both take multiple forms and can have similar effects, though the mechanisms
